    "body": "@chriseth The corpus contains a minimal set cover of all branches covered by test inputs. The minimal set cover across all fuzzers happens to require these many inputs. Moreover, as more code is added, the number of branches increases and so does the set cover.\r\n\r\nWhat I do is fetch the fuzzer corpora from the google database from time to time and push the set cover to the solidity-fuzzing-repo.\r\n\r\n",
